GiT - Decentralized Version Control tool
clone entire repositories on their local systems
Commits are possible even if offline
track changes made to a file and allows you to revert back to any particular change that you wish.

git fetch ->pulls all new commits from the desired branch and
stores it in a new branch in your local repository.

Git pull = git fetch + git merge

file -> edit -> staging area(git add) -> commit(git commit) -> git push to remote repo

Stashing - >your modified tracked files and 
            staged changes and 
            saves it on a stack of unfinished changes.

git diff  - > differences between various commits
git status - > between the working directory and index.


The git config command can be used to change your Git configuration, including your username.

fork -> Open source project -> fork -> my own server side repo
->commit to my repo
->want to merger to original project 
->Pull request

HEAD is used to refer to the last commit in the currently checked-out branch.
index/staging area is a single, large, binary file which lists all files in the current branch.

rebase rewrites the commit history in order to produce a straight, linear succession of commits.
git merge command helps you take the independent lines of development created by git branch 
    and integrate them into a single branch.

Git reset - undo local changes
